data.description: Looking for a mountain side home? Look no further, nestled in the heart of Cumming on 3+ wooded acres.Many quality upgrades by current owner including a lifetime metal roof, paver patio, hot tub, 80 Gal water heater, newer granite in upper kitchen lower kitchenette, auto light bars in all closets plus many more items. Perfect home for multi generational family or teen sweet in the lower level of this unique split level home. No HOA, room for a pool or additional pad to park an RV. This oasis is surrounded by hardwoods and nature, & beautiful landscaping.
data.whatILove:
My wife and I purchased this home because it provided a secluded setting in a community near restaurants, schools, and shopping.   Mountainside subdivision provides that seclusion without going miles and miles outside of town.  Within a year of our purchase an announcement was made that the property at the top of Sawnee Mountain would be deeded to the county for parkland, thus creating an additional level of protection from the continual building of homes with little or no buffer from your next door neighbor.   We also love the fact there is no covenant for the neighborhood.  We are live and let live people and with 3 acers of property, we feel no one should dictate what color our mailbox is or the variety of flowers we grow.  This freedom provides the community with variety and taught our children tolerance for those who are different. 

Here is what you need to know.  If you are a city slicker looking for a fixer upper, this home is not for you.  It has too much property and the interior is country, not city chic, it’s not run down so you can’t afford to rip out the interior to make it something it’s not without being upside down on your mortgage.  It has too much property for anyone without a love for the outdoors.   Planting beds, trees, and open space will leave any city slicker longing for the sound of traffic.   This home is perfect for a professional country couple with or planning to have children.  The large bedrooms are not what you get in a modern layout, so if your teens want their own space, this is for you.  It also has large spaces for family activities and smaller spaces for a quiet evening.  Your neighbors are not right on top of you, so if you want to build a shop, you have the space, if your wife loves flowers; there are 10 different planting beds.  We love this home, but it is time for us to begin our migration to the retirement home at the lake, so we are giving it up for the next couple willing to make their memories in this classic home.
